OL,3,CCouncil's fury at 'unacceptable'
OL,4,Cdelays to flood-hit residents
OL,6,FLeader of Stockport Council,
OL,7,FCouncillor Mark Hunter, and Chief
OL,8,FExecutive Michael Cullen have written
OL,9,Fto the "organisations we believe are
OL,10,Fresponsible" to "act swiftly to
OL,11,Fprovide the support and information
OL,12,Fresidents need".
OL,14,FThey added that the delay in restoring
OL,15,Futilities was "unacceptable" and
OL,16,Fowners Arwal Investments and
OL,17,Fmanagement firm CERT needed to help
OL,18,Fresidents, "many of whom are now in
OL,19,Fcomplete crisis".
